name: food_coach_workspace_v3.3

examples.text: I don't know what to do
had a heavy dinner so not hungry
had an apple but not a real breakfast
no, I had a lunch meeting
list of foods that are not good for you
What are some examples of unhealthy foods?
What would be an example of something that's bad for you?
I had some chicken and rice
yes I remembered to have lunch today

description: A conversation coach for meal monitoring - ensure one eats regularly (meals, snacks), and makes healthy choices.

output.text: This concludes the demo - thank you for trying it out! if you'd like to explore other possible paths in the dialog tree, please vary your emotion and choice of food.
Did you have $time yet?
@food seems like a good choice - it's not on my current list of unhealthy foods.  How do you feel about what you ate?
Hmm...@unhealthy_food.  How do you feel about that food choice?
Hmm...@unhealthy_food is probably not the healthiest choice.  How do you feel about what you ate?
I'm sorry.  I don't understand.  Can you try saying that in another way?
Oh dear.  How do you feel about skipping meals?
That seems like a healthy meal - at least nothing shows up on my list of unhealthy foods.  How do you feel about what you ate?
What did you have?
I'm sorry, I don't recognize anything in your input as a food item. I am still learning. Some food items I understand are, sandwich, bacon, cola. Let's try again.

• I had bacon.
  • I had a sandwich
  • Sandwich and soda

• Satisfied !
  • Somewhat guilty :(
  • Are you kidding me, this is not healthy !!!
Don't worry!  Eating something unhealthy from time to time is okay.  It's only a problem if you make a habit of it.  Don't let it put you off track for the rest of the day! :)
Good, good.  Keep at it!
Hmm.  I'm sorry you don't feel very good about that meal.  Hope you are more satisfied in your other meal choices :)

Hmmm. I'm not entirely sure why you might be unhappy with your food choices. Nothing on your list appears on my list of unhealthy foods. However, it's incomplete. If you need any info on what's healthy versus unhealthy, this might be a good resource to start out with Canada's Food Guide.

It seems you aren't too bothered by the choice.  I assume this is something you don't do on a regular basis, or perhaps you don't care much.  Anyhow, if you're concerned about health, @unhealthy_food is something that should be eaten only in moderation. :)
Mmm.  I feel your pain.  Skipping meals is not fun.  Hunger pangs are overrated.  Try to get something healthy to eat as soon as you can!
Unrepenting!  I get that @unhealthy_food can taste great, but it's not something you want should eat on a regular basis. ;)
Well, you don't appear to be too concerned about it. ;)  It's not the healthiest choice.  Try not to make a habit of it though, unless you don't mind tight pants!
Yes, it's not the best choice, but it's okay to have something unhealthy from time to time.  Everything in moderation!
You seem happy that you missed out on $time!  Why??  Food is wonderful. :)  Try not to make a habit of it.  Skipping meals can backfire horribly. ;)
You seem neither happy nor unhappy. :)
You seem relatively happy. :)  Keep up the good work!
You seem relatively neutral about your choices.  You're doing a good job, keep it up!

values: It's best if you don't skip meals.  Grab something healthy to eat as soon as you can!
Tsk tsk!  Eating regularly is important.  If your blood sugar drops, your ability to make good choices flies out the window.
Eat something healthy soon!  You don't want to find yourself reaching for a Luther burger! :|

Ohhh dear.  If you skip meals, you might find yourself in the In N' Out drive-thru ordering a large animal style fries, a huge milkshake and a 4 x 4.  It might seem like a great idea at the time.  It really isn't. ;)
